  "description_html": "<p>Given the <code>root</code> of a binary tree, return the leftmost value in the last row of the tree.</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong class=\"example\">Example 1:</strong></p>\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://assets.leetcode.com/uploads/2020/12/14/tree1.jpg\" style=\"width: 302px; height: 182px;\" />\n<pre>\n<strong>Input:</strong> root = [2,1,3]\n<strong>Output:</strong> 1\n</pre>\n\n<p><strong class=\"example\">Example 2:</strong></p>\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"https://assets.leetcode.com/uploads/2020/12/14/tree2.jpg\" style=\"width: 432px; height: 421px;\" />\n<pre>\n<strong>Input:</strong> root = [1,2,3,4,null,5,6,null,null,7]\n<strong>Output:</strong> 7\n</pre>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Constraints:</strong></p>\n\n<ul>\n\t<li>The number of nodes in the tree is in the range <code>[1, 10<sup>4</sup>]</code>.</li>\n\t<li><code>-2<sup>31</sup> &lt;= Node.val &lt;= 2<sup>31</sup> - 1</code></li>\n</ul>\n",
